For shortening the URL, we'll use a simple base62 encoding for the `id` column. The base62 encoding will use the characters `[a-zA-Z0-9]`. Here's the helper function:

```php
function base62Encode($num) {
    $base62Chars = 'abcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyzABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ0123456789';
    $encoded = '';

    while ($num > 0) {
