To implement the "load more products" functionality in a React application, you can use a combination of Intersection Observer API, state management with hooks, and conditional rendering. Here's a step-by-step guide to achieve this:

1. First, make sure that you have created a functional component for the list of products and the individual product items.

2. Utilize the `useState` and `useEffect` hooks to manage your component's state and lifecycle. Set an initial state for your products list and a boolean flag for loading status:

```javascript
import React, { useState, useEffect } from "react";

const ProductList = () => {
  const [products, setProducts] = useState([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
};
```

3. Create a function to fetch more products. This function should make an HTTP request to your API, update the `products` state with the new products, and change the `loading` state accordingly:

```javascript
const fetchMoreProducts = async () => {
  setLoading(true);

  // Fetch new products, assuming you have an API that supports pagination
  const response = await fetch("https://api.example.com/products?limit=10&page=" + (products.length / 10 + 1));
  const newProducts = await response.json();

  setProducts([...products, ...newProducts]);
  setLoading(false);
};
```

4. Implement the Intersection Observer to detect when the user has reached the bottom of the list. First, create a `useEffect` hook to set up the observer and a ref for the last product element:

```javascript
import React, { useState, useEffect, useRef } from "react";

// Inside your ProductList component

const lastProductRef = useRef(null);

useEffect(() => {
  const options = {
    root: null,
    rootMargin: "0px",
    threshold: 0.1,
  };

  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    if (entries[0].isIntersecting && !loading) {
      fetchMoreProducts();
    }
  }, options);

  if (lastProductRef.current) {
    observer.observe(lastProductRef.current);
  }

  return () => {
    if (lastProductRef.current) {
      observer.unobserve(lastProductRef.current);
    }
  };
}, [lastProductRef, loading]);
```

